  "prompt": "How do I upload a picture to my little bitty picture window on Quora?",
  "response": "To upload a picture to your profile picture window on Quora, follow these steps:\n\n1. Click on your profile picture in the top right corner of the Quora page.\n\n2. From the dropdown menu, select \"Profile\".\n\n3. On your profile page, click on your current profile picture or the default avatar if you haven't set one yet.\n\n4. A window will appear, allowing you to upload a new picture. Click on \"Upload a photo\".\n\n5. Select the image you want to use from your computer or device. The recommended size for a Quora profile picture is 800 x 800 pixels.\n\n6. After selecting the image, you can adjust and crop it to fit the circular frame. Make sure your face is clearly visible and centered.\n\n7. Once you're satisfied with the positioning, click \"Save\" to set your new profile picture.\n\nRemember that Quora has community guidelines regarding profile pictures, so make sure your image complies with their policies. If you encounter any issues or have further questions, you can refer to Quora's help center for more information.",
